Line an 8X8-inch pan with aluminum foil. Set aside. In a large sauce pan, combine the marshmallow creme, sugar, evaporated milk, butter, and salt. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 4 - 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips. Stir until the chocolate is melted. Stir in the crushed Grasshopper(R) Cookies and vanilla. Pour into lined pan. Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or until firm. Cut into desired shapes or sizes. Serve at room temperature.